		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Context awareness</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Context awareness</b> originated as a term from <a href="/wiki/Ubiquitous_computing" title="Ubiquitous computing">ubiquitous computing</a> or as so-called pervasive computing which sought to deal with linking changes in the environment with computer systems, which are otherwise static. Although it originated as a computer science term, it has also been applied to business theory in relation to <a href="/wiki/Business_process_management" title="Business process management">business process management</a> issues.<sup id="cite_ref-rosemann2006_0-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-rosemann2006-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
